<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6400] SolrCloud tests are not properly testing session expiration.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6400</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are using a test method from the ZK project to pause the connection for a length of time. A while back, I found that the pause time did not really matter. All that happens is that the connection is closed and the zk client creates a new one. So it just causes a dc event, but never reaches expiration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12735888">SOLR-6400</key>
