                            <comment id="14107957" author="andyetitmoves" created="Sat, 23 Aug 2014 09:51:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I made a change with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6370&quot; title=&quot;Allow tests to report/fail on many ZK watches being parallelly requested on the same data&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-6370&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-6370&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to override bits of the test zk server for watch reporting. We could possibly use those hooks to improbably expire connections once in a while. Would add a bit of chaosmonkeyness to all tests..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
